# .gitleaksignore
# Whitelist known false positives so Gitleaks stays blocking
# while not triggering on safe, non-sensitive patterns.
#
# Format: <commit-sha>:<rule-id>
# You can find the rule-id in the Gitleaks JSON report under "RuleID"
#
# HOW TO ADD A FALSE POSITIVE:
# 1. Run a build, download the gitleaks.json report from GCS:
#    gs://postpilot-ai/security-reports/<BUILD_ID>/<service>/gitleaks.json
# 2. Find the entry, copy the "Commit" and "RuleID" fields
# 3. Add a line below in format: <commit>:<rule-id>
#
# Example:
# a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2c3d4e5f6a1b2:generic-api-key
